      "关键词": ["Retrieval-Augmented Generation", "Sequence Generation", "Open-Domain Question Answering", "Language Models", "Constrained Decoding", "Information Retrieval"],
      "摘要": "This paper introduces RICHES, a novel approach that interleaves retrieval with sequence generation tasks. RICHES eliminates the need for separate retriever and generator in conventional RAG systems by retrieving documents through direct decoding of their contents, constrained on the corpus. This unified approach allows adaptation to diverse new tasks via prompting alone, without additional training. RICHES can work with any Instruction-tuned model, provides attributed evidence, supports multi-hop retrievals, and interleaves thoughts to plan retrievals, all within a single decoding pass of the LLM. The authors demonstrate RICHES' strong performance across open-domain question answering tasks, including attributed and multi-hop QA.",
